  "body": "Prysm bazel build does not support archLabs (likely also will not support Arch-Linux).\r\nWhen I try to build on my system running \"ArchLabs\" I get the following logs:\r\n```\r\n[me@mysystem prysm]$ bazel build //beacon-chain:beachon-chain\r\nStarting local Bazel server and connecting to it...\r\nINFO: Repository llvm_toolchain instantiated at:\r\n  /mnt/teraByteDisk/teraByteDisk/prysm/prysm/WORKSPACE:29:15: in <toplevel>\r\nRepository rule llvm_toolchain defined at:\r\n  /home/me/.cache/bazel/_bazel_me/ef3f60115dbd95e5e1d7dfbf229016bc/external/com_grail_bazel_toolchain/toolchain/rules.bzl:24:33: in <toplevel>\r\nERROR: An error occurred during the fetch of repository 'llvm_toolchain':\r\n   Traceback (most recent call last):\r\n\tFile \"/home/me/.cache/bazel/_bazel_me/ef3f60115dbd95e5e1d7dfbf229016bc/external/com_grail_bazel_toolchain/toolchain/internal/configure.bzl\", line 102, column 37, in llvm_toolchain_impl\r\n\t\t_download_llvm_preconfigured(rctx)\r\n\tFile \"/home/me/.cache/bazel/_bazel_me/ef3f60115dbd95e5e1d7dfbf229016bc/external/com_grail_bazel_toolchain/toolchain/internal/llvm_distributions.bzl\", line 120, column 17, in download_llvm_preconfigured\r\n\t\tfail(\"Failed to detect host OS version: \\n%s\\n%s\" % (exec_result.stdout, exec_result.stderr))\r\nError in fail: Failed to detect host OS version: \r\n\r\nUnsupported linux distribution and version: ArchLabs, 2019.10.29\r\nERROR: no such package '@llvm_toolchain//': Failed to detect host OS version: \r\n\r\nUnsupported linux distribution and version: ArchLabs, 2019.10.29\r\nINFO: Elapsed time: 2.379s\r\nINFO: 0 processes.\r\nFAILED: Build did NOT complete successfully (0 packages loaded)\r\n```\r\n<!--💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎\r\n\r\nHellooo! 😄 \r\n\r\nTo help us tend to your issue faster, please search our currently open issues before submitting a new one.\r\nExisting issues often contain information about workarounds, resolution, or progress updates.\r\n\r\n💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎